      "span_text": "An Irish study examined survey data before and after a ban on POS displays and advertising in July 2009.  Post ban, children were significantly less likely to overestimate peer smoking prevalence compared to pre ban, which suggests that the removal of POS tobacco displays may contribute to the denormalization of tobacco products among children.",
